AGI -&nbsp; Chinese President Xi Jinping> received Russian Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov> at the conclusion of his two-day visit to Beijing. The meeting between Xi and Lavrov took place after a press conference in which the head of Kremlin diplomacy and its Chinese counterpart, Wang Yi>, made an account of yesterday's official talks, which dealt with issues such as conflicts in Ukraine and Gaza. The two ministers agreed that the relations between Beijing and Moscow have strengthened, agreed their position on the main global geopolitical challenges and stressed that both countries will fight "hegemony and intimidating behaviour", an explicit reference to the United States. According to Chinese media, Lavrov would prepare the ground for a mission in China by Vladimir Putin>. The first foreign trip of the Russian President after the re-election would be scheduled for next month.
&nbsp;
Wang and Lavrov reaffirmed the importance of a truce in the Middle East and their support for the creation of a Palestinian State. During the joint press conference at the end of the bilateral meeting, Wang said that the recent resolution of the UN Security Council on the ceasefire in Gaza, on which the United States did not veto, is "winner" and "mandatory". The Chinese Foreign Minister called for "support to the Palestinian nation in the creation of a state" so that "a Jewish nation and an Arab nation can coexist peacefully". &nbsp;
&nbsp;
"China will support Russia's stable development under Putin's leadership. Beijing and Moscow will continue to strengthen strategic cooperation on the world stage and provide strong mutual support," said the highest Chinese diplomat. Lavrov, for his part, has stamped as "useless" international meetings on the war in Ukraine, which do not take into account the interests of Moscow and promote only the Kiev peace proposal. "We and our Chinese friends clearly affirm the need to take into account the legitimate concerns of all parties involved, mainly in the security sector. In this context, we, together with our Chinese colleagues, have confirmed that any international event is useless: not only do they not take into account the position of Russia, but ignore them completely by promoting the so-called "formula of peace" of the absolutely empty ultimatum of Volodymyr Zelensky and are therefore completely separated from reality", said the Russian minister in the press conference in Beijing.
&nbsp;
Lavrov recalled that the West "is applying illegal sanctions against a number of states, including obviously Russia", and added that "this policy is beginning to be actively applied towards China".
